sequenceDiagram
    participant W as workload thread tree
    participant K as kernel proc connector
    participant N as tid_monitor
    participant M as pmu_monitor callback
    participant L as lbr slot manager
    participant D as next lbr_drain()

    W->>K: clone() or fork() creates new TID
    K-->>N: PROC_EVENT_FORK / child_tid
    N->>N: tracked_contains(parent_tid or parent_tgid)
    N->>M: on_tid_born(child_tid)
    M->>L: lbr_add_tid(child_tid)
    L->>L: open perf_event + mmap ring buffer
    L-->>M: new LBR slot active
    M-->>N: return
    D->>L: iterate active slots
    L-->>D: child thread branch samples included
    W->>K: thread exit
    K-->>N: PROC_EVENT_EXIT / tid
    N->>M: on_tid_dead(tid)
    M->>L: lbr_remove_tid(tid)
